 *
 * <h2>Performance</h2>
 * All fixed-width header fields are read directly from the backing {@link java.nio.ByteBuffer}
 * without copying. Iteration over uncompressed records is similarly zero-copy. Compressed records
 * are decoded lazily through {@link #streamingIterator(org.apache.kafka.common.utils.BufferSupplier)}
 * or eagerly (with full decompression into a temporary list) through {@link #iterator()}.
