     * Return a read-only duplicate of the {@link java.nio.ByteBuffer} that backs this instance.
     *
     * <p>The returned buffer shares the same underlying byte array (or memory-mapped region) as
     * the original but has its own independent position, limit, and mark. Callers must not write
     * to the returned buffer. Changes to position or limit on the returned duplicate do not
